y bring together the best and most current research on their topics, while series editor Donald Lopez provides an introduction to the volume as a whole. In addition to providing a wealth of detail on the history, doctrine, and practice of the religions of Asia, the five chapters offer an opportunity for sustained discussions of the category of "religion."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0areligion orientale. 7aRELIGION / Buddhism / General (see also PHILOSOPHY / Buddhist).2bisacsh  aAtharva Veda.  aBhakti.  aBrahman.  aBritish Period.  aBuddhism.  aBureaucracy.  aChristianity.  aConfucianism.  aDaoism.  aEthical Practices.  aHinduism.  aIndo-Aryans.  aJainism.  aKinship.  aLotus Sūtra.  aMahābhārata.  aMuḥammad.  aPadmasambhava.  aReligions of China.  aReligions of Japan.  aSacrifice and Society.  aSakya.  aSufis.  aTantra.  aVeda.  aViṣṇu.  aYajur Veda.  aYoga.  adharma.  anirguṇa.  anirvāṇa.  asaguṇa.  asaṃsāra.1 aDavis, Richard H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLopez Jr., Donald S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLopez, Donald S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLopez, Jr., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTanabe, Jr., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTeiser, Stephen F, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691214788zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691214788423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691214788.jpg  a978-3-11-044249-6  Prin